  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Should we deprecate our hash utils package and just use go-ethereum/common? common package is thoroughly tested works and has good helper methods. @rauljordan mentioned crypto/sha3 package is different than the one ETH1.0 client uses.\r\n\r\nFor background and history, there was an EIP back to standardize hashes and the decision was made to not use a standard sha3 implementation that hare out there and instead use a modified keccak256 which lives in common package. Currently, all ETH1.0 client use the modified keccak256.\r\n\r\n@nisdas has raised a question on whether `common.BytesToHash` hashes or simply converts byte slice into 32 byte array. He is doing more investigation so tentatively assigning this to him.\r\n\r\nReference: https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/blob/master/EIPS/eip-55.md",
